"n. (剑或刀之)柄 【英】 n. (剑或刀之)柄(the handle of a sword) 【记】 参考haft(柄); shaft(矛柄) n. (武器或工具的)手柄 = handle 【参】haft(n 工具或武器的柄); shaft(n 柄矛或箭杆) 【记】haft 柄；held, hold 拿的东西 handle hilt (n.)  Old English hilt ""hilt, handle of a sword or dagger,"" from Proto-Germanic *helt (cognates: Old Norse hjalt, Old High German helza ""hilt,"" Old Saxon helta ""oar handle""), perhaps from PIE *kel- (1) ""to strike."" Formerly also used in plural in same sense as singular."
